<TEXT>
<P>
I watch Keith Olbermann (KCBS) because I will see something I won't see 
anywhere else -- humor. 
</P>
<P>
His work is original, he has a clever play on words and sometimes he's just 
plain silly. 
</P>
<P>
More than this, he places events in historical perspective with a knowledge of 
tradition and an obvious love of the games. 
</P>
<P>
And since in all this there is a recognition that the viewer might actually 
have some intelligence and awareness of sports and something beyond, I will 
continue to watch Keith Olbermann. 
</P>
<P>
Lulu Lewis, North Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
