<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOVIET TROOPS IN GERMANY LOAD POTATOES FOR HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAMBURG, Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soviet troops based in what was East Germany will help load ships with German 
potatoes to make up for a harvest shortfall in their homeland. 
</P>
<P>
About 100 Soviet soldiers will come to the northern port city of Hamburg each 
day to load six ships with 100,000 tons of potatoes, a harbor authority 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Another 500,000 tons will be shipped from Baltic ports in eastern Germany, also 
with Soviet military help. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
