<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUIET AMERICAN WINS IN 1:32 4/5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quiet American, bumped from the field in the Breeders' Cup, ran the fourth 
fastest mile ever in New York on Saturday in winning the $638,000 NYRA Mile at 
Aqueduct in 1:32 4/5. 
</P>
<P>
The 4-year-old colt, a grandson of record-holder Dr. Fager (1:32 1/5), took the 
lead at the start, was eased back, then came on again to retake the lead 
entering the stretch. Through the stretch, Quiet American widened his advantage 
to 4 3/4 lengths, carrying 116 pounds and ridden by Chris McCarron. 
</P>
</TEXT>
