<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRINGLE, UMBERG INSPIRE 'NO' VOTE ON TERM LIMITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Curt Pringle, the incumbent assemblyman from the 72nd Assembly District, admits 
that he and his campaign workers intentionally distributed campaign literature 
known to contain false statements. 
</P>
<P>
In short, he admits he lied to the voters. 
</P>
<P>
What's his excuse? That the material was already printed. 
</P>
<P>
No wonder the California Journal, when ranking 79 Assembly members, put Pringle 
among the bottom 10 in integrity and the bottom 12 in brains. 
</P>
<P>
KARLA LOUISE BELL, Newport Beach 
</P>
