<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLDEN WEST DOMINATES, WINS WATER POLO TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Golden West College, the second-ranked water polo team in the state, defeated 
Pasadena, 20-3, Saturday at Belmont Plaza in Long Beach to win the South Coast 
Conference championship. 
</P>
<P>
Edvard Van Luijin had six goals, and Tory Culbertson and Brian Sciacca had 
three goals apiece for the Rustlers (26-3), who had a 12-1 lead at the half and 
led 18-1 after three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals and finals, Golden West outscored its opponents, 41-7. 
</P>
<P>
The Rustlers return to Belmont Plaza Friday and Saturday for the Southern 
California Regional playoffs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
