<HEADLINE>
<P>
'A' IS FOR AWFUL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shearer doesn't seem to realize that a school is only as good as the community 
around it. Unfortunately, parents just don't seem to care. 
</P>
<P>
Anyone who has been in elementary schools lately would see that the teachers 
are considered not educators but day-care providers. Children are often dropped 
off at school 45 minutes before school begins -- when there is no adult 
supervision -- and left to roam after school until parents return from work. 
</P>
<P>
In short, we do not need people such as Shearer who sit around and complain 
about public schools. We need people to get involved. Join the PTA, run for the 
school board, or vote; the choice is yours whether or not our schools will 
succeed. 
</P>
<P>
KATHY MACK 
</P>
<P>
Burbank 
</P>
</TEXT>
