<HEADLINE>
<P>
'A' IS FOR AWFUL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harry Shearer (Man Bites Town, " 'A' Is for Awful," Sept. 16) claims that the 
only individuals who are in our public schools today are "people who have no 
choice." 
</P>
<P>
Let me correct him. Speaking for myself and many fellow colleagues, we have 
chosen to remain teachers because we care about America's future and wish to 
contribute to our nation's success. We have not given up to find work 
elsewhere. Unlike Shearer, we have chosen to stay and fight. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD HALSEY 
</P>
<P>
Escondido 
</P>
</TEXT>
