<HEADLINE>
<P>
'A' IS FOR AWFUL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I took time to read this "awful" attack against the public school system and 
its teachers before I spent: 
</P>
<P>
1. 
</P>
<P>
Two hours grading papers and working on report cards. 
</P>
<P>
2. Three hours preparing weekly lesson plans. 
</P>
<P>
3. Two hours filling in referrals for psychological screening of potentially 
gifted and learning disabled children. 
</P>
<P>
4. One hour writing communiques to parents. 
</P>
<P>
During my "vacation" I will attend the California Reading Assn. Conference, put 
in time at my region office and take a couple of in-service classes. 
</P>
<P>
I'm not one of two teachers in my school who are "good"; I'm one of at least 
30. 
</P>
<P>
CAROLYN RORMAN 
</P>
<P>
Dana Point 
