<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE READERS RESPOND TO 'MOVIEMAKERS, MOVIE CRITICS AND YOU'; 
</P>
<P>
THE CHICKEN OR THE EGG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The comments defining the moviemakers' primary audience as the "under-25 age 
group" seem to more reflect their decision to play to that group than the fact 
that anyone over 25 is less interested and will spend less money to go to the 
movies. 
</P>
<P>
Maybe the decrease in interest among those of us in that category is because 
Hollywood doesn't try for something beyond violence, motor car chases, 
bed-hopping, etc. There are some really good films, but one has to be on the 
alert and search. That's where the critic comes in. 
</P>
<P>
MARILYN AVERY, Calabasas 
</P>
</TEXT>
