<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE READERS RESPOND TO 'MOVIEMAKERS, MOVIE CRITICS AND YOU'; 
</P>
<P>
THEY GIVE FRANKLIN LESS THAN A 10 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Of all the movie critics in town whose recommendations are suspect, the worst 
offender is television's Gary Franklin. 
</P>
<P>
It used to be that Franklin gave rave reviews sparingly, but it seems as though 
half the full- and double-page ads for major movies now feature a quote from 
Franklin calling some movie "a 10" or "10 plus." 
</P>
<P>
Because we all know that barely a dozen movies a year truly are that good, it 
is ludicrous to believe Franklin when he implies that so many films are among 
the greatest of all time. 
</P>
<P>
His obvious zeal for getting his name in print destroys his credibility. 
</P>
<P>
JIM BOYD, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
