<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN MARCOS' PATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Marcos is at a crossroads, and the election Nov. 6 may well determine which 
direction it will take. 
</P>
<P>
The city can either continue on its pell-mell growth pattern, with no concern 
about the pleas of residents for reasonable, lower-density development. Or it 
can respect the wishes of residents by choosing the path that retains many of 
the characteristics that have made San Marcos unique. 
</P>
<P>
The only City Council member who has been dedicated to protecting residents' 
rights and quality of life is Pia Harris. I have known Pia for 21 years, and 
she keeps her word to voters. She cares about people and about San Marcos. 
</P>
<P>
MIA URBACH, San Marcos 
</P>
</TEXT>
