<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 CHARGED WITH MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 12-year-old San Marcos boy led sheriff's deputies to the home of two men who 
he said had repeatedly raped and sexually abused him Friday night after luring 
him away from a San Marcos taco shop to a house in a remote area of the city. 
</P>
<P>
The youth, whose name was withheld because of his age, was abducted by the two 
men about 6 Friday evening and finally released by the men four hours later 
several miles from the house where he had been sexually assaulted. 
</P>
<P>
The boy found his way back home and told his parents about the attack. 
</P>
<P>
The 12-year-old was able to lead the deputies back to his attackers' house and 
to describe the type of car they were driving. Sheriff's investigators obtained 
a search warrant and entered the suspects' house about 8 a.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Evidence seized included adult pornographic videotapes and items of clothing 
believed to have been worn by the suspects at the time of the assault on the 
youth. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested and jailed on charges of kidnap, child molestation, sodomy, oral 
copulation and displaying pornographic material to children are Warren Patrick 
Derichweiler, 24, and Miguel Chavez, 21. 
</P>
<P>
Both are being held at the Vista detention facility in lieu of bail, which was 
set at $160,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
