<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANYON FIRE CONTAINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Civilian and military fire units contained a brush fire early Saturday morning 
that burned 1,500 acres in the Margarita Canyon area near Camp Pendleton, a 
Marine Corps spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
More than 30 fire units quickly responded to reports of a fire in a remote area 
approximately 2 miles from Meadow Creek Deluz housing area Friday afternoon, 
public affairs spokesman Sgt. Rene Reyna said. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters controlled the blaze around 2 a.m. Saturday. There was no 
structural damage. 
</P>
<P>
"The fire is well-contained," he said. "Now it's a matter of letting it take 
its course, waiting for it to die out." 
</P>
<P>
One firefighter suffered a sprained ankle and another received cuts while 
battling the flames, Reyna said. The cause of the fire is under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
