<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: ENCINITAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Encinitas woman was allegedly kidnaped from her home by a former boyfriend 
just moments after calling 911 for help Saturday morning, a Sheriff's spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Donna Marie Maloney, 36, of the 100 block of Phoebe Street, called 911 at 7:55 
a.m. Saturday and said "Sonny" was kicking in her door. 
</P>
<P>
The phone was then disconnected. 
</P>
<P>
The first Sheriff's deputy to the scene arrived three minutes after Maloney's 
call was placed and found the door kicked in, the telephone disconnected and no 
one inside the apartment. A witness said Wilmer "Sonny" Evans Hart Jr., 43, of 
Encinitas, led Maloney to her car, a 1984 tan over gold Dodge 600 convertible 
with license plate number 1JWM820, and ordered her to get in the back seat. 
Maloney complied and Hart drove away in the car. 
</P>
<P>
Maloney and Hart had apparently had a tumultuous relationship over the past 
three weeks, capped last Sunday by Maloney filing a temporary restraining order 
prohibiting Hart to contact her. Maloney claimed Hart assaulted her. 
</P>
<P>
The missing woman is described as white, with shoulder-length brown wavy hair 
and brown eyes, 5 foot 7 inches and 128 pounds. She was wearing a long white 
nightgown. The suspect is a white man, 6 foot 3 inches and 210 pounds with 
blondish-gray shoulder-length hair and blue eyes and a Fu Manchu-style 
mustache. 
</P>
<P>
Anyone with information on the whereabouts of Hart and Maloney is asked to call 
Sheriff's Homicide Detail at 565-5200. 
</P>
</TEXT>
