<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Municipal Court judge is under investigation after admitting she secretly 
dated a police officer, whom she later married, while he was a key prosecution 
witness in a drug case she handled. 
</P>
<P>
The Commission on Judicial Performance is investigating Judge Irene Takahashi, 
said Municipal Judge Julie Conger, who is now handling the drug case. Takahashi 
said she did not reveal her affair with El Cerrito Officer Michael Ramirez as 
she should have before an October, 1989, preliminary hearing. Takahashi said 
her failure to disclose the relationship deprived two defendants of their 
constitutional right to a fair and impartial hearing. 
