<P>
INGLEWOOD SELECTS DEVELOPMENT HEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Inglewood officials Friday named a former Los Angeles County development 
specialist, Jesse J. Lewis, as the city's new director of development. 
</P>
<P>
Lewis, who will begin the new post Dec. 3, will help create new development 
projects. He will also head the city's efforts to redevelop areas under the 
flight path of Los Angeles International Airport and to build low- and 
moderate-income housing, city officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Development has been a key issue in Inglewood, which has experienced a boom in 
residential building in some areas but lags in commercial projects in the 
downtown area. 
</P>
<P>
In his post with the Los Angeles Community Development Commission, Lewis worked 
on projects that included a shopping center and single-family and multifamily 
housing developments. 
</P>
