<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NEWS: NEW CLINIC TO STUDY ENGINEERING PROBLEMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal Poly Pomona's College of Engineering has opened an Engineering 
Interdisciplinary Clinic to help solve engineering problems for industry. 
</P>
<P>
The clinic has received $90,000 for three projects being sponsored by Southern 
California Gas Co., General Dynamics Air Defense Systems and Hughes Aircraft 
Co. 
</P>
<P>
The first project is a study of the possible carcinogenic chemicals produced by 
auto engines modified to use natural gas. 
</P>
<P>
The second is a look at more effective methods of manufacturing semiconductors, 
and the third is a study of how to modernize a communications interface, a 
device used for military applications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
