<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LOSS DIMS AZUSA PACIFIC'S HOPES FOR POSTSEASON BERTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Brian Hunt turned in a record-setting performance but Azusa 
Pacific's hopes for a playoff berth probably ended Saturday when UC Santa 
Barbara defeated the Cougars, 27-23, in a nonconference game at Azusa Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
Azusa Pacific, which had been in contention for a berth in the National Assn. 
of Intercollegiate Athletics Division II playoffs, dropped to 5-2. 
</P>
<P>
Hunt completed 40 of 62 passes for 416 yards, eclipsing the school record of 
369 yards that was set by Greg Gano in 1978. 
</P>
<P>
Hunt has passed for 2,324 yards this season, breaking Gano's record of 1,918 
that also was set in 1978. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Curtius completed 15 of 37 for 291 yards and three touchdowns for Santa 
Barbara (6-3). 
</P>
<P>
Claremont 27, Whittier 22 -- Schon Branum gained 140 yards in 26 carries and 
scored on a 31-yard run to lead the Stags over the Poets in a Southern 
California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference game at Claremont. 
</P>
<P>
Quarterback Brian O'Brien completed 15 of 22 for 210 yards and connected with 
Tim Bray on touchdown plays of 12 and four yards for Claremont (2-6, 2-3). 
</P>
<P>
Doi Johnson, a 290-pound fullback, gained 41 yards in 12 carries and scored on 
touchdown runs of six yards and one yard for Whittier (0-8, 0-5). 
</P>
<P>
La Verne 44, Pomona-Pitzer 7 -- Jeff Paschal completed 12 of 32 for 290 yards 
and three touchdowns to lead the Leopards (3-5, 2-3) over the Sagehens (3-4, 
2-2) in an SCIAC game at La Verne. 
</P>
<P>
Paschal connected on touchdown passes of four and 51 yards to Rod Zerbel and 62 
yards to Chris Nance. 
</P>
<P>
Nance, who gained 195 yards in 28 carries, also scored on a 36-yard run. 
</P>
</TEXT>
