HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF KRIEGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
El Segundo 21, Bell-Jeff 0 -- El Segundo (5-3-1, 2-2) held Bell-Jeff to 37 
rushing yards and allowed the Guards to reach Eagle territory only once in a 
San Fernando Valley League game at Burroughs High. 
</P>
<P>
El Segundo reached the end zone on a 17-yard run by Don Smith and a 53-yard run 
by Chris Fenney that gave the Eagles a 14-0 halftime lead. For Bell-Jeff (1-8, 
1-2), Anthony Pawluc completed 14 of 28 passes for 120 yards and suffered two 
interceptions. JEFF KRIEGER 
</P>
