HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB SONNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
St. Francis 28, St. Genevieve 0 -- St. Francis limited St. Genevieve to one 
first down and 43 yards of total offense at Birmingham High, leaving the 
Valiants winless in San Fernando Valley League competition. 
</P>
<P>
St. Francis (6-3, 2-1) scored in the first quarter on a 22-yard Shawn Haney run 
and added three touchdowns in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Larry Duenas and quarterback John Willis ran for scores of one and two yards. 
The Golden Knights scored again less than a minute after Willis' run when 
Valiant quarterback/punter Bobby Kite fumbled the snap at his two-yard line and 
St. Francis linebacker Marty Konrad picked up the loose ball with :23 left in 
the half. ROB SONNER 
</P>
